cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with wireless communication and information theory, specifically the broadcast channel with delayed channel state information and coded caching. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also involves networked systems and communication, which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as another likely category. The use of caching and optimization techniques may also place the paper in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis and performance evaluation, which may make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
